content:
I'm trying to use Quickbooks Pro, but I while updating the software it asked me to enter my license number, but I cant seem to find it. How do I get back into my program? I bought it a few months ago on Sept 14, 2023. I'll be presenting the end of the year and fourth quarter goals in our team meeting next week and I won't be able to compile the data without access to this. Also, we had some issues in our last meeting where the camera would focus on the door and not on any of the people at the door. What was happening here? Has this been fixed. The ID for that camera is 195.256.74.65. 

Read the customer utterance above and identify all intents IDs and then extract the appropriate entities for that intent. The intent ID is the first value for each item in the set of intents and entities. If there is not a value for an entity, put "None" in its place instead. If there are not any intents found within the customer utternance, the intent ID should be "iuektbjk87o5yiuw" and you should not put anything down for the entities. 

Your output should be a nested list in YAML formatting with the intent ID as the initial key and the entity ID (key)and extracted value (value) as the nested list under the intent ID.

chosen:
7fcf7ed7c1034c158:
    b6ab16dae6e34702b : Quickbooks Pro
    iiekng37349jdkfl : 09.14.2023
ca25da49740f4f51a:
    4d541ed05f1d471cb : "None"
    b14606ba11ee43e78 : "camera"
    c39d2a2a73834d558 : "None"
    f575b2c62547449b9 : "195.256.74.65"
